  faq={[
    {
      q: 'How does Invisalign compare to traditional braces?',
      a: 'Invisalign aligners are virtually invisible, removable, and don\'t have wires or brackets that irritate the cheeks. Treatment time is comparable for most cases. Braces may be more appropriate for very severe bite corrections, but Invisalign can treat the vast majority of alignment issues including overbites, underbites, crossbites, crowding, and spacing.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How long does Invisalign treatment take?',
      a: 'Most adult cases complete in 12–18 months. Minor corrections can be done in as little as 6 months. The exact timeline depends on the complexity of your case and how consistently you wear your aligners — the recommendation is 20–22 hours per day.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Does Invisalign hurt?',
      a: 'Most patients experience mild pressure or soreness for 1–3 days each time they switch to a new aligner set — this is normal and means the treatment is working. There are no sharp wires, so soft tissue irritation is much less common than with braces.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Can I eat and drink with Invisalign?',
      a: 'You remove your aligners to eat and drink anything other than plain water. This means no food restrictions. Just brush your teeth before putting the aligners back in, and rinse the aligners before reinserting them.',
    },
    {
      q: 'How much does Invisalign cost in Bayside, NY?',
